text: Thryptomene podantha is a shrub species in the family Myrtaceae that is endemic to Western Australia. The shrub is found in the Mid West and Gascoyne regions of Western Australia between Geraldton and Shark Bay. ==References== podantha Category:Endemic flora of Western Australia Category:Rosids of Western Australia Category:Plants described in 2014 Category:Taxa named by Barbara Lynette Rye Category:Taxa named by Malcolm Eric Trudgen
